1
00:00:05,196 --> 00:00:08,090
One child with multiple traumatic injuries,
in cardiopulmonary arrest.

2
00:00:08,130 --> 00:00:10,850
Five hospitals have already refused.
Please accept the patient.

3
00:00:12,243 --> 00:00:15,203
No good. We can't find a hospital.

4
00:00:19,790 --> 00:00:22,390
You really hate being on call
in the ER that much?

5
00:00:22,470 --> 00:00:26,196
A resident doctor on call on his first day?
That's insane.

6
00:00:26,236 --> 00:00:28,070
I hope we don't get anyone
with cardiac arrest.

7
00:00:28,110 --> 00:00:31,590
Relax. We don't take critical patients here.

8
00:00:32,090 --> 00:00:34,370
Cardiac arrests and other serious cases are

9
00:00:34,410 --> 00:00:36,190
all sent to other hospitals.

10
00:00:36,230 --> 00:00:38,050
Is that really okay?

11
00:00:38,225 --> 00:00:39,876
Director's orders.

12
00:00:40,063 --> 00:00:43,870
He doesn't want us taking critical cases
and risking malpractice suits.

13
00:00:44,716 --> 00:00:47,750
So we're only allowed to accept patients
who seem easy to save.

14
00:00:48,043 --> 00:00:51,930
Well, lucky me, I guess.

15
00:00:52,463 --> 00:00:56,103
Oh, but Dr. Ashura's on duty today.

16
00:00:56,643 --> 00:00:57,849
Ashura?

17
00:01:00,090 --> 00:01:01,296
Yep.

18
00:01:17,666 --> 00:01:20,743
"An Ashura dwells in the ER."

19
00:01:21,800 --> 00:01:24,560
That's the rumor going around the hospital.

20
00:01:26,380 --> 00:01:29,960
They're talking about Dr. Shura Anno,
an emergency physician.

21
00:01:45,880 --> 00:01:47,459
She's gorgeous.

22
00:01:49,486 --> 00:01:50,706
Whoa!

23
00:01:53,326 --> 00:01:54,529
Incoming.

24
00:01:56,040 --> 00:01:57,245
What?

25
00:02:00,620 --> 00:02:01,826
Dr. Anno!

26
00:02:07,739 --> 00:02:09,580
Were you dreaming or something?

27
00:02:10,376 --> 00:02:11,583
Huh?

28
00:02:12,072 --> 00:02:14,636
- Hello?
- Female, in her 30s, fell down the stairs.

29
00:02:14,676 --> 00:02:17,732
Cardiac arrest in the ambulance.
Requesting emergency transport.

30
00:02:18,940 --> 00:02:20,293
My patient.

31
00:02:21,666 --> 00:02:22,780
Bring her in now.

32
00:02:22,820 --> 00:02:25,530
Wait! We don't accept cardiac arrest cases!

33
00:02:25,570 --> 00:02:26,776
Get ready, now!

34
00:02:27,517 --> 00:02:28,730
What?!

35
00:02:36,590 --> 00:02:37,610
Any changes?

36
00:02:37,650 --> 00:02:38,776
Still in cardiac arrest.

37
00:02:38,816 --> 00:02:40,022
Going up!

38
00:02:40,180 --> 00:02:44,640
One, two, three, four, five,
six, seven, eight, nine, ten.

39
00:02:44,793 --> 00:02:49,293
One, two, three, four, five,
six, seven, eight, nine, twenty.

40
00:02:49,366 --> 00:02:50,972
- Climbing down.
- Okay.

41
00:02:51,579 --> 00:02:52,620
On three.

42
00:02:52,660 --> 00:02:53,920
One, two, three.

43
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:56,360
Cutting the clothes.

44
00:02:57,420 --> 00:03:00,223
- Prepare the DC and set it to 150.
- Yes.

45
00:03:02,120 --> 00:03:04,665
Um, what should I do?

46
00:03:04,705 --> 00:03:06,273
Monitor ventilation and IV fluids.

47
00:03:06,400 --> 00:03:07,606
Yes!

48
00:03:11,273 --> 00:03:12,480
Thirty.

49
00:03:14,043 --> 00:03:15,043
Switching in.

50
00:03:15,070 --> 00:03:16,363
- All yours.
- Got it.

51
00:03:16,840 --> 00:03:18,160
The DC charge is ready.

52
00:03:23,670 --> 00:03:24,896
- Let go.
- Yes.

53
00:03:29,850 --> 00:03:31,950
- Reassess in two minutes. Charge 200.
- Yes.

54
00:03:38,930 --> 00:03:40,570
Move.

55
00:03:47,196 --> 00:03:48,236
Save him!

56
00:03:48,276 --> 00:03:49,810
Save the boss!

57
00:03:50,500 --> 00:03:51,790
Yakuza.

58
00:03:53,033 --> 00:03:54,286
Oxygen!

59
00:03:54,620 --> 00:03:55,780
Yes!

60
00:03:55,820 --> 00:03:58,813
Gunshot? Don't you have
your own back-alley doctor?

61
00:03:59,300 --> 00:04:00,707
What'd you say?!

62
00:04:00,747 --> 00:04:03,039
Ah, Kansai boys.
Kid, prep a blood transfusion.

63
00:04:03,079 --> 00:04:04,726
Huh? Me?

64
00:04:04,766 --> 00:04:06,356
- Hemostasis, too.
- Huh?

65
00:04:06,396 --> 00:04:11,072
Hey! Our boss comes first!
Treat him before that woman!

66
00:04:11,112 --> 00:04:12,529
Her heart's stopped!

67
00:04:13,531 --> 00:04:15,845
His heart is still beating.
Kid, stop the bleeding!

68
00:04:16,743 --> 00:04:17,920
I can't do it!

69
00:04:17,960 --> 00:04:19,166
What?!

70
00:04:19,992 --> 00:04:21,430
Understood.

71
00:04:32,110 --> 00:04:33,323
Beat!

72
00:04:35,276 --> 00:04:36,496
Beat!

73
00:04:36,858 --> 00:04:38,383
- Two minutes passed.
- DC!

74
00:04:41,689 --> 00:04:42,962
- Clear!
- Yes!

75
00:04:52,785 --> 00:04:56,246
Heartbeat’s back. Intubate, ventilate,
monitor blood oxygenation, and page Surgery.

76
00:04:56,286 --> 00:04:57,505
Understood.

77
00:04:59,359 --> 00:05:01,320
The bleeding won't stop!

78
00:05:06,230 --> 00:05:08,436
- What's going on?
- Blood pressure's 60!

79
00:05:10,290 --> 00:05:11,476
Stop bleeding!

80
00:05:11,516 --> 00:05:13,636
Why ain't you operatin' on him?!

81
00:05:13,676 --> 00:05:16,136
- I'm just a resident!
- Like we care, idiot!

82
00:05:16,176 --> 00:05:20,983
Dr. Anno! Her heartbeat's back, right?
Please, come help here!

83
00:05:22,190 --> 00:05:25,235
Headache, vomiting, and no response
in the right pupil to light.

84
00:05:25,275 --> 00:05:32,476
Bilateral pupil dilation. Likely right
acute subdural hematoma. No-filling sign.

85
00:05:32,516 --> 00:05:35,630
You mean no blood flow to the brain?!

86
00:05:35,670 --> 00:05:37,576
We decompress now, or she dies.

87
00:05:37,616 --> 00:05:38,896
What?!

88
00:05:38,943 --> 00:05:43,570
Doctor! Neurosurgery's unavailable!
No OR opening for two hours!

89
00:05:46,283 --> 00:05:50,810
- It's on us. Prep the CT and trepanation.
- Yes!

90
00:05:50,850 --> 00:05:56,110
Surgery? Here? On the brain?!

91
00:05:56,150 --> 00:05:59,090
Brain cells die in five minutes.
No time to wait for a neurosurgeon!

92
00:06:13,430 --> 00:06:14,736
- Pean.
- Here.

93
00:06:16,743 --> 00:06:18,810
She's really doing it here.

94
00:06:18,870 --> 00:06:20,070
Retractor.

95
00:06:23,839 --> 00:06:26,370
Doctor! VT!

96
00:06:26,650 --> 00:06:29,280
Boss! Hang in there!

97
00:06:29,320 --> 00:06:31,010
Kid! Start cardiac massage now!

98
00:06:31,553 --> 00:06:32,960
- Huh?
- Now!

99
00:06:33,900 --> 00:06:34,940
Yes!

100
00:06:34,980 --> 00:06:36,430
- That one.
- Right.

101
00:06:41,412 --> 00:06:42,672
Boss...

102
00:06:50,102 --> 00:06:51,190
What?

103
00:06:51,230 --> 00:06:52,863
Treat the boss first!

104
00:06:55,023 --> 00:06:56,196
Huh?!

105
00:06:56,236 --> 00:06:59,583
Are you stupid?
If I die, your boss dies, too.

106
00:07:01,756 --> 00:07:03,703
- Damn it!
- Kid! DC!

107
00:07:04,690 --> 00:07:05,890
Yes!

108
00:07:06,530 --> 00:07:07,736
Step back!

109
00:07:13,019 --> 00:07:14,953
- Success!
- Resume cardiac massage!

110
00:07:15,460 --> 00:07:16,665
Yes!

111
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:19,860
Twenty!

112
00:07:21,560 --> 00:07:22,793
Thirty!

113
00:07:27,143 --> 00:07:29,403
Forget the other patient!

114
00:07:30,977 --> 00:07:32,477
Save the boss!

115
00:07:41,210 --> 00:07:43,436
Don’t point that gun at my patient!

116
00:07:51,245 --> 00:07:53,090
- Drain, please.
- Yes!

117
00:08:04,290 --> 00:08:07,050
This'll reduce the brain pressure.
Prep the laparotomy set.

118
00:08:07,110 --> 00:08:08,330
Yes!

119
00:08:16,956 --> 00:08:18,222
- Scalpel.
- Here.

120
00:08:23,537 --> 00:08:24,823
- Retractor.
- Here.

121
00:08:25,156 --> 00:08:26,643
So much blood.

122
00:08:26,683 --> 00:08:27,889
Suction.

123
00:08:28,470 --> 00:08:29,676
Yes.

124
00:08:34,590 --> 00:08:37,036
As I thought, the abdominal aorta is damaged.

125
00:08:37,076 --> 00:08:39,023
What? What do we do?

126
00:08:39,063 --> 00:08:40,736
- Get a vascular graft ready.
- Yes!

127
00:08:41,450 --> 00:08:43,910
A vascular graft? You can't mean...!

128
00:08:43,976 --> 00:08:47,090
We'll excise the damaged section
and reconstruct it with a graft.

129
00:08:47,290 --> 00:08:50,310
Aortic surgery here? That's impossible!

130
00:08:50,696 --> 00:08:52,930
Doctor! Let’s call
the vascular surgery department!

131
00:08:52,970 --> 00:08:54,236
Kid, suction!

132
00:08:55,649 --> 00:08:56,763
Now!

133
00:08:56,803 --> 00:08:57,850
Yes!

134
00:08:57,890 --> 00:08:59,669
I've got the vascular graft!

135
00:09:17,750 --> 00:09:21,590
Incredible. First the brain,
now aortic surgery...

136
00:09:22,763 --> 00:09:24,263
And she is so fast.

137
00:09:39,003 --> 00:09:40,203
Done.

138
00:09:50,299 --> 00:09:51,599
The waveform is back!

139
00:09:55,920 --> 00:09:57,206
Heartbeat restored.

140
00:09:57,499 --> 00:10:00,063
- Boss!
- That was incredible!

141
00:10:00,653 --> 00:10:02,260
Pack it and do a temporary closure.

142
00:10:02,613 --> 00:10:05,563
We reopen as soon as an OR is free.
Add more transfusions.

143
00:10:05,623 --> 00:10:06,829
Understood!

144
00:10:08,286 --> 00:10:10,463
- She did it!
- He'll survive!

145
00:10:12,640 --> 00:10:15,696
She treated two patients simultaneously,
all by herself.

146
00:10:17,807 --> 00:10:19,073
So this is...

147
00:10:19,599 --> 00:10:20,826
Ashura.

148
00:10:41,610 --> 00:10:43,856
Thank goodness they both survived.

149
00:10:44,050 --> 00:10:46,750
But this is insane for a first day.

150
00:10:46,983 --> 00:10:49,343
Dr. Ashura's always like this.

151
00:10:49,370 --> 00:10:50,590
Always?

152
00:10:50,910 --> 00:10:54,083
So my entire
three-month training here will be like today?

153
00:10:54,970 --> 00:10:56,870
What is with that doctor?

154
00:11:06,620 --> 00:11:09,460
Back then, I had no idea.

155
00:11:10,714 --> 00:11:13,456
I didn't know why this doctor,
whom they called Ashura,

156
00:11:17,295 --> 00:11:21,571
fought on the battlefield known
as emergency medicine.

157
00:11:29,749 --> 00:11:35,149
Dr. Ashura

158
00:11:35,696 --> 00:11:37,749
I am so sorry!

159
00:11:37,980 --> 00:11:39,420
You surprised me.

160
00:11:40,615 --> 00:11:44,140
Two critical patients were accepted
in a single night...

161
00:11:44,180 --> 00:11:46,410
I am deeply sorry!

162
00:11:47,300 --> 00:11:49,363
What's wrong with saving patients?

163
00:11:49,980 --> 00:11:52,583
The ER is facing a severe doctor shortage.

164
00:11:53,050 --> 00:11:55,856
We're barely managing with a skeleton crew.

165
00:11:55,896 --> 00:11:58,010
Because everyone quit thanks to you.

166
00:11:58,050 --> 00:12:02,576
We can't provide proper care
for critical patients under these conditions.

167
00:12:03,036 --> 00:12:05,260
This rule exists to protect patients.

168
00:12:05,300 --> 00:12:06,660
I saved them, so what?

169
00:12:06,700 --> 00:12:08,303
They survived by luck.

170
00:12:08,760 --> 00:12:11,416
One mistake and it could've been malpractice.

171
00:12:12,580 --> 00:12:16,123
I will not have a lawsuit on my watch.

172
00:12:16,163 --> 00:12:18,923
So it's just self-preservation.

173
00:12:18,963 --> 00:12:21,890
- Anno, wait.
- A warning for you both.

174
00:12:24,756 --> 00:12:29,563
Dr. Anno, one more incident like this,
and you'll face disciplinary termination.

175
00:12:30,610 --> 00:12:35,270
Shuji Daikoku, you will be demoted
from Head of the Emergency Department.

176
00:12:35,310 --> 00:12:36,490
Demoted?!

177
00:12:36,530 --> 00:12:38,790
No, please, anything but that.

178
00:12:38,830 --> 00:12:40,743
You get one chance.

179
00:12:42,110 --> 00:12:43,330
You understand?

180
00:12:47,130 --> 00:12:48,389
Is that all?

181
00:12:50,689 --> 00:12:51,915
Later.

182
00:12:55,156 --> 00:13:00,090
I'm terribly sorry.
I'll have a stern talk with her later.

183
00:13:00,756 --> 00:13:02,130
Please do.

184
00:13:03,170 --> 00:13:07,030
The ER is already a financial burden
with its constant deficits.

185
00:13:07,890 --> 00:13:10,963
I don't want any more unnecessary trouble.

186
00:13:11,190 --> 00:13:13,150
Understood!

187
00:13:15,456 --> 00:13:16,956
Disciplinary termination?!

188
00:13:17,090 --> 00:13:19,770
That means "fired," right?

189
00:13:20,023 --> 00:13:21,690
Isn't it just a bluff?

190
00:13:21,730 --> 00:13:23,316
I hope so.

191
00:13:23,356 --> 00:13:26,575
Why does the director have it out

192
00:13:26,615 --> 00:13:28,710
He wants to get back
to Touou University Hospital.

193
00:13:28,750 --> 00:13:29,803
What do you mean?

194
00:13:29,843 --> 00:13:33,137
He lost the professor election last year
and got kicked out of Touou Hospital.

195
00:13:33,830 --> 00:13:37,110
He doesn't want any trouble
that could hurt his chances of going back.

196
00:13:37,150 --> 00:13:40,995
Accepting critical patients does raise
the risk of mistakes.

197
00:13:41,035 --> 00:13:44,002
Plus, our deficit is an eyesore to him.

198
00:13:44,042 --> 00:13:46,560
Oh! I'll take Ms. Ogura to Surgery.

199
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:48,247
- I'll go, too!
- Sure, off you go.

200
00:13:48,950 --> 00:13:51,980
You're being moved to Surgery,
where your recovery will be monitored.

201
00:13:53,750 --> 00:13:58,883
So I won't be staying
in the ER the whole time?

202
00:13:59,136 --> 00:14:04,156
The ER handles initial treatment.
Once you're stable, you move to a specialist.

203
00:14:05,763 --> 00:14:07,163
I see.

204
00:14:08,190 --> 00:14:11,830
Anno... Anno...
I have to do something about Anno.

205
00:14:11,870 --> 00:14:14,323
Hey! Dr. Daikoku!

206
00:14:14,363 --> 00:14:16,930
Dr. Kongo, good job.

207
00:14:16,970 --> 00:14:18,203
Likewise.

208
00:14:18,569 --> 00:14:19,770
No, that's not it.

209
00:14:20,543 --> 00:14:27,283
The patients brought to the ER yesterday...
Surgery will take over both of them.

210
00:14:27,295 --> 00:14:28,434
Thank you.

211
00:14:28,474 --> 00:14:30,823
You're welcome. No, that's not it.

212
00:14:31,270 --> 00:14:34,923
Honestly, we've got our hands full
with the patients we already have.

213
00:14:35,050 --> 00:14:38,503
I'd appreciate it if you stopped
sending us more patients.

214
00:14:38,643 --> 00:14:39,643
I'm sorry.

215
00:14:39,670 --> 00:14:41,295
An apology is all I need.

216
00:14:41,335 --> 00:14:43,196
No, that's not it.

217
00:14:43,796 --> 00:14:45,029
That's not it.

218
00:14:45,550 --> 00:14:50,036
You accept patients on your own,
then dump them on us without follow-through.

219
00:14:50,383 --> 00:14:53,050
What a cushy job. I'm envious.

220
00:14:53,090 --> 00:14:55,336
Maybe I should transfer to the ER.

221
00:14:55,376 --> 00:14:57,463
No, that's not it.

222
00:14:58,877 --> 00:15:01,696
That's not it. That's not what I meant.

223
00:15:04,850 --> 00:15:07,056
I'm Kongo,
the Head of the Surgery Department.

224
00:15:07,256 --> 00:15:11,376
We will take full responsibility
for your treatment. Please rest assured.

225
00:15:12,103 --> 00:15:15,930
Thank you so much.

226
00:15:15,936 --> 00:15:17,149
Mommy!

227
00:15:19,070 --> 00:15:20,776
Hina.

228
00:15:21,190 --> 00:15:22,863
I missed you!

229
00:15:22,903 --> 00:15:26,949
Sae! Thank goodness!

230
00:15:27,270 --> 00:15:31,610
Doctor, thank you so much
for saving my daughter.

231
00:15:31,850 --> 00:15:33,990
I can't thank you enough.

232
00:15:34,030 --> 00:15:37,210
Not at all. I only did what any doctor would.

233
00:15:37,390 --> 00:15:39,816
Thank you so much.

234
00:15:40,170 --> 00:15:41,510
Thank you, Doctor.

235
00:15:41,596 --> 00:15:43,256
Don't bother... No, that's not it.

236
00:15:43,797 --> 00:15:45,197
You're welcome.

237
00:15:45,350 --> 00:15:46,790
This isn't right.

238
00:15:47,157 --> 00:15:52,377
The ER saved Ms. Ogura, so why is
Surgery getting all the thanks?

239
00:15:53,290 --> 00:15:56,470
Well, that's how it always is for the ER.

240
00:15:58,283 --> 00:16:00,863
Other departments swoop in
and take the credit.

241
00:16:01,730 --> 00:16:03,783
So unrewarding.

242
00:16:06,176 --> 00:16:09,276
Regarding the establishment
of the International Taishaku Hospital...

243
00:16:09,316 --> 00:16:14,016
Our prospects for securing funding are dire,
and there's no timeline for opening.

244
00:16:14,196 --> 00:16:17,055
Chairwoman, the cause
of the funding rejection is without a doubt

245
00:16:17,095 --> 00:16:19,983
the 300-million-yen annual deficit generated
by the ER.

246
00:16:20,570 --> 00:16:25,783
To realize your dream of the new hospital,
we have no choice but to shut down the ER.

247
00:16:25,836 --> 00:16:26,836
Shut it down?

248
00:16:26,870 --> 00:16:28,636
Chairwoman, please wait.

249
00:16:30,410 --> 00:16:32,576
Chairwoman, what do you think?

250
00:16:39,340 --> 00:16:44,960
Actually, I've called in my trump card.

251
00:16:45,380 --> 00:16:46,593
Trump card?

252
00:16:47,533 --> 00:16:48,933
Come in, please.

253
00:17:03,593 --> 00:17:06,460
Chairwoman, who is this?

254
00:17:07,366 --> 00:17:11,586
This is Dr. Makoto Tamon,
former Head of the Emergency Department.

255
00:17:12,150 --> 00:17:15,583
He's been working in overseas
medical operations these past years,

256
00:17:15,796 --> 00:17:20,096
but I've brought him back as Vice Director
and Head of the Medical Department.

257
00:17:20,323 --> 00:17:22,503
- Vice Director?
- Head of the Medical Department?

258
00:17:22,756 --> 00:17:26,436
Director Fudo,
please take good care of Dr. Tamon.

259
00:17:27,310 --> 00:17:28,536
Of course.

260
00:17:28,770 --> 00:17:31,670
Director, I look forward to working with you.

261
00:17:32,010 --> 00:17:33,276
Likewise.

262
00:17:38,533 --> 00:17:41,133
What? Dr. Tamon is back?

263
00:17:41,320 --> 00:17:43,823
And as vice director, no less.
Can you believe it?

264
00:17:44,899 --> 00:17:47,319
Good news for you, Dr. Anno.

265
00:17:48,339 --> 00:17:50,819
The ER's future is secure now.

266
00:17:51,700 --> 00:17:53,000
Maybe so.

267
00:17:56,540 --> 00:17:58,080
Is he really that amazing?

268
00:17:59,666 --> 00:18:04,486
He was Dr. Anno's mentor.
Dr. Ashura must be relieved, too.

269
00:18:04,759 --> 00:18:05,759
Huh?

270
00:18:05,786 --> 00:18:09,710
She's been fighting alone
ever since Dr. Tamon left.

271
00:18:15,900 --> 00:18:22,003
Ashura is a god of war and protection
who will surely defend the ER.

272
00:18:26,836 --> 00:18:31,200
When I come back, let's change
emergency care in Japan together.

273
00:18:33,670 --> 00:18:34,883
Yes.

274
00:18:35,252 --> 00:18:36,572
See you then.

275
00:19:06,239 --> 00:19:10,303
Gather the best doctors,
provide cutting-edge medicine,

276
00:19:10,661 --> 00:19:12,828
and attract VIP patients
from around the world...

277
00:19:13,090 --> 00:19:14,890
That won't be easy.

278
00:19:15,339 --> 00:19:21,383
Even so, International Taishaku Hospital will
become a reality, no matter what.

279
00:19:21,895 --> 00:19:24,456
I'm counting on you, Dr. Tamon.

280
00:19:24,503 --> 00:19:28,865
I won't let you down.
But about that promise...

281
00:19:28,905 --> 00:19:30,151
Of course.

282
00:19:32,672 --> 00:19:36,955
I always keep my promises.

283
00:19:38,330 --> 00:19:39,616
Thank you.

284
00:19:51,603 --> 00:19:54,600
I'm on call with Dr. Anno again today.

285
00:19:54,640 --> 00:19:57,658
Listen! No trouble tonight, you hear me?!

286
00:19:57,698 --> 00:19:59,319
Increase noradrenaline to eight.

287
00:19:59,359 --> 00:20:01,973
- Check BP in 15 minutes and adjust the rate.
- Understood.

288
00:20:02,013 --> 00:20:03,986
- Hey, listen!
- What?

289
00:20:04,220 --> 00:20:06,300
Do you even grasp how serious this is?

290
00:20:06,820 --> 00:20:08,122
You'll be fired!

291
00:20:08,162 --> 00:20:13,230
If I get demoted because of you,
I'm done for! Listen to me!

292
00:20:17,743 --> 00:20:18,950
Incoming.

293
00:20:20,610 --> 00:20:22,410
- Wait!
- Hello?

294
00:20:22,543 --> 00:20:27,083
Female, 40s, found unconscious on the street.
Now in cardiopulmonary arrest.

295
00:20:27,310 --> 00:20:28,523
Understood.

296
00:20:29,330 --> 00:20:31,390
We can't treat her. Take her elsewhere.

297
00:20:31,430 --> 00:20:33,070
You want to abandon a patient again?

298
00:20:33,610 --> 00:20:35,123
Director's orders.

299
00:20:35,156 --> 00:20:36,616
You just don't want a demotion.

300
00:20:36,656 --> 00:20:38,156
It's for patient safety!

301
00:20:38,341 --> 00:20:41,710
We don't have the manpower
to handle critical patients!

302
00:20:41,750 --> 00:20:43,476
I'm all you need.

303
00:20:43,651 --> 00:20:47,981
What if you make a mistake?
The whole ER takes the fall!

304
00:20:48,021 --> 00:20:50,970
The patient's between life and death.
Nothing else matters!

305
00:20:58,369 --> 00:20:59,729
Bring her in now.

306
00:21:00,630 --> 00:21:03,143
Kid, get the ultrasound
and resuscitation kit ready.

307
00:21:03,570 --> 00:21:05,530
- Yes, Doctor!
- Do what you want!

308
00:21:14,836 --> 00:21:16,856
Ow...

309
00:21:22,217 --> 00:21:25,530
Dr. Ashura accepted
another critical care patient, didn't she?

310
00:21:25,570 --> 00:21:28,016
She's beyond my control now.

311
00:21:29,416 --> 00:21:33,343
She reminds me
of how you used to be, Dr. Daikoku.

312
00:21:33,990 --> 00:21:35,195
Huh?

313
00:21:35,763 --> 00:21:37,276
Good work today.

314
00:21:45,750 --> 00:21:50,963
Professor, if you need help
with research funding, just say the word.

315
00:21:51,435 --> 00:21:52,755
I'm happy to help.

316
00:21:54,223 --> 00:21:55,370
What's this?

317
00:21:55,410 --> 00:21:59,396
Just a small gift. Please, help yourself.

318
00:22:02,860 --> 00:22:06,636
By the way, about that matter we discussed...

319
00:22:07,542 --> 00:22:12,380
I'd be most grateful for your support
in returning to Touou University Hospital.

320
00:22:13,060 --> 00:22:16,630
If you had some
suitable achievements to show...

321
00:22:16,860 --> 00:22:18,150
I understand.

322
00:22:18,665 --> 00:22:25,010
I'll make the new hospital a reality
and achieve flawless results to show you.

323
00:22:25,150 --> 00:22:29,743
That said, I hear you are
struggling to raise funds?

324
00:22:31,020 --> 00:22:36,320
Don't worry. Shutting down
the ER will solve everything.

325
00:22:36,620 --> 00:22:41,056
But the chairwoman brought back
the former ER chief, didn't she?

326
00:22:41,325 --> 00:22:43,883
Doesn't seem like she intends
to close the ER.

327
00:22:50,210 --> 00:22:51,696
I'm exhausted.

328
00:22:54,903 --> 00:22:55,903
Ugh!

329
00:22:55,936 --> 00:22:57,636
Stay away from me!

330
00:22:58,970 --> 00:23:00,530
You got a thing for me?

331
00:23:00,623 --> 00:23:02,151
I said, let me go!

332
00:23:02,249 --> 00:23:03,682
Hey, stop it, please!

333
00:23:03,722 --> 00:23:05,470
Let me go!

334
00:23:05,510 --> 00:23:07,430
Please calm down!

335
00:23:07,470 --> 00:23:08,556
You look tasty!

336
00:23:08,596 --> 00:23:10,736
Ow!

337
00:23:18,290 --> 00:23:19,816
Ow!

338
00:23:19,856 --> 00:23:21,016
Sorry.

339
00:23:21,056 --> 00:23:23,770
We should've just turned that drunk away.

340
00:23:23,810 --> 00:23:26,463
Once they're here, they become a patient.

341
00:23:28,116 --> 00:23:30,575
I'm starving. Got anything?

342
00:23:31,923 --> 00:23:33,123
I'll take this.

343
00:23:33,296 --> 00:23:35,376
Wait, that's been sitting there
since yesterday.

344
00:23:36,450 --> 00:23:38,123
- Tasty.
- She's wild.

345
00:23:41,253 --> 00:23:43,033
Was it spoiled after all?

346
00:23:45,890 --> 00:23:47,096
Incoming.

347
00:23:49,590 --> 00:23:50,710
Stretcher coming through!

348
00:23:50,750 --> 00:23:53,336
Male, in his 20s, in severe shock
from traffic injuries!

349
00:23:53,376 --> 00:23:54,630
One, two, three!

350
00:23:55,150 --> 00:23:57,410
- Start oxygen, prep him!
- Yes!

351
00:23:57,450 --> 00:23:58,656
Cutting the clothes.

352
00:24:07,120 --> 00:24:09,223
Doctor! The bleeding won't stop!

353
00:24:09,263 --> 00:24:11,180
Arterial hemostasis. Irrigate the wound.

354
00:24:11,360 --> 00:24:12,446
Get K3 ready.

355
00:24:12,486 --> 00:24:14,693
- Page the orthopedics and anesthesia teams.
- Yes.

356
00:24:19,640 --> 00:24:21,260
Where am I?! Let me outta here!

357
00:24:21,300 --> 00:24:23,008
Mr. Tanaka, let's go rest over there.

358
00:24:23,048 --> 00:24:24,563
Shut up!

359
00:24:29,360 --> 00:24:30,950
Hey, Doc!

360
00:24:35,480 --> 00:24:38,180
Well, aren't you a pretty doctor?

361
00:24:38,220 --> 00:24:39,530
Can I get a kiss?

362
00:24:39,700 --> 00:24:41,690
You're interfering with treatment!

363
00:24:44,920 --> 00:24:46,580
Get an upper endoscope ready now.

364
00:24:46,689 --> 00:24:48,109
- Endoscope?
- Now.

365
00:24:48,149 --> 00:24:49,149
Yes, Doctor.

366
00:24:49,174 --> 00:24:52,060
Dr. Anno, we don't need an endoscope
for arterial hemostasis, do we?

367
00:24:52,100 --> 00:24:53,370
Let go of me!

368
00:25:02,470 --> 00:25:03,735
He's vomiting blood?!

369
00:25:03,913 --> 00:25:05,113
Mr. Tanaka!

370
00:25:05,170 --> 00:25:06,956
Huh? Why?

371
00:25:06,996 --> 00:25:08,716
Esophageal variceal rupture.

372
00:25:09,050 --> 00:25:10,050
What?

373
00:25:10,080 --> 00:25:12,380
Jaundice in the eyes.
Spider angioma on the chest.

374
00:25:12,420 --> 00:25:14,760
Palmar erythema.
It's textbook liver cirrhosis.

375
00:25:14,856 --> 00:25:16,456
With elevated portal pressure,

376
00:25:16,496 --> 00:25:18,640
varices are easily predictable.

377
00:25:18,700 --> 00:25:19,980
As is their rupture.

378
00:25:20,840 --> 00:25:22,079
Wait...

379
00:25:23,500 --> 00:25:25,420
You examined him earlier?

380
00:25:25,680 --> 00:25:27,440
Doctor! Endoscope is ready!

381
00:25:27,523 --> 00:25:28,890
- Set it there.
- Yes!

382
00:25:31,300 --> 00:25:32,643
No way...

383
00:25:32,653 --> 00:25:35,656
She knew he'd vomit blood
and asked for the endoscope.

384
00:25:36,000 --> 00:25:37,293
Amazing.

385
00:25:37,540 --> 00:25:38,900
In that one moment...

386
00:25:39,000 --> 00:25:40,620
She saw all of this coming.

387
00:25:45,040 --> 00:25:46,363
Doctor, he's stopped breathing.

388
00:25:46,403 --> 00:25:47,853
- Ambu bag.
- Yes.

389
00:25:50,380 --> 00:25:51,599
What do I do?

390
00:25:52,520 --> 00:25:53,520
They're both critical.

391
00:25:53,545 --> 00:25:56,488
Kid, buy time on that drunk with an SB tube.

392
00:25:59,603 --> 00:26:03,296
I can stop the bleeding.

393
00:26:04,683 --> 00:26:06,370
- You?
- Have you done it before?

394
00:26:06,410 --> 00:26:08,730
I trained in GI before coming here!

395
00:26:09,210 --> 00:26:10,710
Scope, please!

396
00:26:15,536 --> 00:26:16,963
Here, and...

397
00:26:18,010 --> 00:26:19,716
- Here. Electric scalpel.
- Yes.

398
00:26:35,102 --> 00:26:36,589
All right.

399
00:26:37,836 --> 00:26:39,836
I can finally be useful.

400
00:26:42,956 --> 00:26:47,483
For esophageal varices,
first-line treatment is EVL.

401
00:26:47,660 --> 00:26:49,725
Attach a rubber band
to the tip of the scope,

402
00:26:49,765 --> 00:26:53,556
suction the bleeding site,
and stop the bleeding with the rubber band.

403
00:26:54,340 --> 00:26:56,010
Stay calm.

404
00:26:58,773 --> 00:26:59,986
Where is it?

405
00:27:01,439 --> 00:27:03,130
The bleeding site.

406
00:27:09,310 --> 00:27:10,610
Found it.

407
00:27:14,746 --> 00:27:15,950
Now!

408
00:27:17,173 --> 00:27:18,373
Do it, please!

409
00:27:18,740 --> 00:27:19,946
Yes!

410
00:27:22,658 --> 00:27:23,864
Good.

411
00:27:27,370 --> 00:27:28,589
We did it!

412
00:27:28,690 --> 00:27:29,782
- Pean.
- Here.

413
00:27:29,822 --> 00:27:32,336
Dr. Anno, hemostasis achieved!

414
00:27:34,115 --> 00:27:35,335
Huh?

415
00:27:38,423 --> 00:27:39,650
Why...

416
00:27:40,602 --> 00:27:42,942
Did the band come off?

417
00:27:43,170 --> 00:27:44,275
BP's dropping!

418
00:27:44,315 --> 00:27:46,056
Enough! Use the SB tube!

419
00:27:49,843 --> 00:27:51,243
I'll stop it this time!

420
00:27:57,823 --> 00:27:58,830
Hurry.

421
00:27:58,870 --> 00:28:00,450
Hurry! Hurry!

422
00:28:01,362 --> 00:28:03,110
Hurry, hurry.

423
00:28:05,750 --> 00:28:06,956
Hurry.

424
00:28:07,976 --> 00:28:09,183
Hurry!

425
00:28:11,038 --> 00:28:12,083
Hurry!

426
00:28:12,123 --> 00:28:13,329
Tamotsu!

427
00:28:16,944 --> 00:28:18,629
BP's in the 40s!

428
00:28:18,669 --> 00:28:19,810
Damn!

429
00:28:19,850 --> 00:28:22,643
Why, why, why?!

430
00:28:30,940 --> 00:28:32,180
Doctor.

431
00:28:33,180 --> 00:28:34,576
This is beyond you, kid.

432
00:28:36,356 --> 00:28:39,580
I can do it! Give me one more chance!

433
00:28:39,620 --> 00:28:41,480
There are no second chances here!

434
00:28:58,360 --> 00:29:00,023
It's still there.

435
00:29:00,680 --> 00:29:02,596
Deeper, maybe.

436
00:29:05,400 --> 00:29:06,626
The stomach?

437
00:29:08,120 --> 00:29:10,653
There was nothing there before.

438
00:29:14,460 --> 00:29:15,660
Found it.

439
00:29:17,687 --> 00:29:20,946
How?! It wasn't bleeding before!

440
00:29:20,986 --> 00:29:24,760
Stopping the upper bleed shifted
the pressure, causing bleeding elsewhere.

441
00:29:30,620 --> 00:29:31,833
Do it!

442
00:29:32,260 --> 00:29:33,460
Yes!

443
00:29:56,780 --> 00:29:58,770
BP's back up!

444
00:30:02,253 --> 00:30:06,940
No other bleeding sites.
Let's monitor for now. Move him to the ICU.

445
00:30:06,980 --> 00:30:08,183
Got it!

446
00:30:15,450 --> 00:30:16,930
I'm sorry.

447
00:30:17,763 --> 00:30:21,603
You got cocky, stopping one bleed,
and missing what was right in front of you.

448
00:30:22,490 --> 00:30:26,810
Only those who can imagine
every possible outcome can save lives.

449
00:30:31,430 --> 00:30:33,803
You're not ready for the battlefield.

450
00:30:39,180 --> 00:30:41,096
Doctor! Another transport request!

451
00:30:41,400 --> 00:30:42,500
Accept immediately.

452
00:30:42,540 --> 00:30:43,750
Yes.

453
00:31:09,883 --> 00:31:11,920
Here. Good work.

454
00:31:12,939 --> 00:31:14,163
Thanks.

455
00:31:16,793 --> 00:31:19,750
Man, that was rough, huh?

456
00:31:20,870 --> 00:31:22,123
I was...

457
00:31:23,423 --> 00:31:25,440
completely useless.

458
00:31:27,799 --> 00:31:29,459
I just held everyone back.

459
00:31:33,570 --> 00:31:36,776
Your shift's over. Go home and sleep.

460
00:31:39,426 --> 00:31:41,386
Yeah, I will.

461
00:31:42,083 --> 00:31:46,223
Kid, check the variceal patient's blood work
and order a transfusion.

462
00:31:46,236 --> 00:31:47,876
CT scan for the accident patient.

463
00:31:51,051 --> 00:31:52,420
What are you doing? Move.

464
00:31:52,680 --> 00:31:53,886
Hang in there.

465
00:31:59,963 --> 00:32:00,970
Good morning.

466
00:32:01,010 --> 00:32:02,210
Morning!

467
00:32:06,830 --> 00:32:09,790
Oh, let me make some coffee.

468
00:32:12,337 --> 00:32:13,543
Sorry!

469
00:32:15,396 --> 00:32:16,602
Incoming.

470
00:32:18,570 --> 00:32:19,783
Hey!

471
00:32:21,843 --> 00:32:26,350
Emergency! Tunnel Seven collapsed.
Multiple casualties!

472
00:32:29,690 --> 00:32:32,990
Dr. Daikoku, what do we do?

473
00:32:48,430 --> 00:32:53,310
Leave critical patients to other hospitals.
We only accept minor injuries.

474
00:32:55,703 --> 00:32:56,990
Accept all of them. Now.

475
00:32:57,030 --> 00:32:58,230
All of them? Are you insane?!

476
00:32:58,270 --> 00:32:59,417
Patients are waiting.

477
00:32:59,457 --> 00:33:02,116
No way! We don't even have enough beds!

478
00:33:02,156 --> 00:33:05,730
You'd abandon patients for that?
We can figure out the beds.

479
00:33:05,770 --> 00:33:10,403
I'm in charge here! You don't get to decide!

480
00:33:19,026 --> 00:33:21,710
Tell them we can't accept critical patients.

481
00:33:22,872 --> 00:33:25,132
Please! We've been rejected
five times already!

482
00:33:25,940 --> 00:33:27,160
We can't find a hospital.

483
00:33:27,612 --> 00:33:28,858
We can't accept.

484
00:33:29,113 --> 00:33:30,113
We can't.

485
00:33:30,140 --> 00:33:32,256
We can't treat critical patients.

486
00:33:41,420 --> 00:33:42,620
What?

487
00:33:43,666 --> 00:33:46,410
No matter what you say,
my answer won't change.

488
00:33:53,383 --> 00:33:54,700
Huh?

489
00:33:54,740 --> 00:33:56,020
Hey, Anno!

490
00:33:57,946 --> 00:33:59,446
Stop it, please!

491
00:33:59,659 --> 00:34:01,103
Let me go!

492
00:34:02,720 --> 00:34:05,236
- What is this?!
- We're going to the scene. Drive.

493
00:34:08,007 --> 00:34:09,250
What?

494
00:34:33,369 --> 00:34:35,189
Are you okay?

495
00:34:56,936 --> 00:34:58,136
Can you hear me?

496
00:35:05,763 --> 00:35:06,963
Let's go.

497
00:35:08,037 --> 00:35:09,249
Yes.

498
00:35:11,123 --> 00:35:15,263
Chest wall bulging, jugular vein distension.
Tension pneumothorax.

499
00:35:16,320 --> 00:35:17,920
There's a hole in the lung?

500
00:35:18,270 --> 00:35:20,716
Air's leaking out,
making it impossible to breathe.

501
00:35:20,756 --> 00:35:22,363
We need to release the trapped air.

502
00:35:22,660 --> 00:35:23,880
- Scissors.
- Here!

503
00:35:27,759 --> 00:35:29,070
- Disinfectant.
- Here.

504
00:35:30,203 --> 00:35:32,289
- Surflo, 14 gauge.
- Yes.

505
00:35:33,510 --> 00:35:34,716
This one?

506
00:35:34,736 --> 00:35:36,503
Found it. Here you go.

507
00:36:10,268 --> 00:36:11,916
- Yes!
- Transport him to a hospital.

508
00:36:11,956 --> 00:36:12,956
Understood.

509
00:36:12,983 --> 00:36:14,980
One with minor injuries has been rescued.

510
00:36:15,020 --> 00:36:16,220
Medics are over here.

511
00:36:16,743 --> 00:36:18,696
We'll take over. Are you okay?

512
00:36:19,776 --> 00:36:22,726
Thank you for saving my daughter.

513
00:36:22,766 --> 00:36:23,780
That woman...

514
00:36:23,820 --> 00:36:26,630
Please, let me go back in.

515
00:36:27,103 --> 00:36:28,183
We can't allow that.

516
00:36:28,223 --> 00:36:30,323
But...

517
00:36:30,693 --> 00:36:31,733
What happened?

518
00:36:31,773 --> 00:36:32,980
Dr. Anno.

519
00:36:33,600 --> 00:36:35,760
My granddaughter is still inside!

520
00:36:35,940 --> 00:36:37,209
What?!

521
00:36:38,286 --> 00:36:40,570
She's impaled on a rebar and can't move!

522
00:36:41,680 --> 00:36:44,283
Please, save Hina!

523
00:36:45,499 --> 00:36:47,780
- Kid, let's go.
- Yes!

524
00:36:47,820 --> 00:36:51,045
You can't. There's a risk
of secondary collapse inside.

525
00:36:51,085 --> 00:36:53,138
The patient's condition may be critical.

526
00:36:53,178 --> 00:36:56,205
Orders from HQ. We can't let you in.

527
00:36:56,245 --> 00:36:58,339
They're right, Dr. Anno.
Let's follow their orders.

528
00:36:58,379 --> 00:37:00,425
The patient is between life and death.

529
00:37:01,040 --> 00:37:03,220
I can't just abandon a life.

530
00:37:09,330 --> 00:37:10,330
Move.

531
00:37:10,355 --> 00:37:11,581
Doctor!

532
00:37:12,956 --> 00:37:14,156
Excuse me!

533
00:37:21,410 --> 00:37:22,989
Start CPR.

534
00:37:26,150 --> 00:37:28,030
It's dangerous. Please, get out!

535
00:37:28,070 --> 00:37:29,296
The patient?

536
00:37:32,026 --> 00:37:33,646
- Hey, wait...
- Hina!

537
00:37:34,259 --> 00:37:35,459
Hina!

538
00:37:35,985 --> 00:37:37,186
Can you hear me?

539
00:37:38,600 --> 00:37:40,760
Cardiac arrest. What's the rescue status?

540
00:37:40,800 --> 00:37:43,200
A rebar has pierced her abdomen.
We can't move her.

541
00:37:43,220 --> 00:37:46,080
We'll clear the debris
and carry her out with the rebar.

542
00:37:46,120 --> 00:37:47,543
- Wait.
- Huh?

543
00:37:47,772 --> 00:37:49,886
I'll do a thoracotomy, stop the bleeding,
and do CPR.

544
00:37:49,926 --> 00:37:51,166
Thoracotomy?!

545
00:37:51,900 --> 00:37:55,300
We need to get out now!
We should focus on the rebar first!

546
00:37:55,340 --> 00:37:57,813
She dies unless we restart
her heart immediately!

547
00:37:57,853 --> 00:38:00,440
Can't you just do it without opening her up?!

548
00:38:00,480 --> 00:38:03,386
Without hemostasis, she'll hemorrhage
once her heart restarts!

549
00:38:03,393 --> 00:38:06,420
It'll take one minute.
Kid, get the line and open the IV.

550
00:38:07,813 --> 00:38:09,013
Got it!

551
00:38:32,860 --> 00:38:34,073
You okay?

552
00:38:34,180 --> 00:38:35,393
I'm fine.

553
00:38:38,916 --> 00:38:41,959
Clamping the aorta to stop the bleeding.
Ventilate and add epinephrine.

554
00:38:41,980 --> 00:38:43,193
Got it!

555
00:38:59,240 --> 00:39:00,446
Huh?

556
00:39:00,880 --> 00:39:03,000
Cardiac massage in this state?

557
00:39:03,580 --> 00:39:05,000
No way...

558
00:39:07,260 --> 00:39:10,856
Open cardiac massage by hand!

559
00:39:12,853 --> 00:39:14,053
Beat.

560
00:39:15,647 --> 00:39:16,886
Come on!

561
00:39:17,630 --> 00:39:18,930
Come on!

562
00:39:19,720 --> 00:39:20,920
Come on!

563
00:39:25,170 --> 00:39:26,389
Come on!

564
00:39:32,193 --> 00:39:33,430
Come on!

565
00:39:43,700 --> 00:39:45,816
Doctor! Hurry!

566
00:39:54,970 --> 00:39:56,223
Good.

567
00:39:57,310 --> 00:39:58,516
Let's go.

568
00:39:58,756 --> 00:39:59,962
Huh?

569
00:40:12,350 --> 00:40:15,190
Yes! Heartbeat restored!

570
00:40:15,230 --> 00:40:17,209
- Remove the rebar!
- Yes!

571
00:40:20,240 --> 00:40:21,510
One, two, three!

572
00:40:22,340 --> 00:40:24,660
- Let's get out of here!

573
00:40:28,860 --> 00:40:29,880
Cardiac arrest?!

574
00:40:29,920 --> 00:40:32,090
- Put her down! Gloves!
- Yes!

575
00:40:46,683 --> 00:40:47,896
Why?

576
00:40:49,150 --> 00:40:51,391
Her heartbeat restarted...

577
00:41:05,220 --> 00:41:06,453
Kid, grab the bag!

578
00:41:07,840 --> 00:41:09,046
Oh, okay!

579
00:41:09,640 --> 00:41:10,853
No, that one!

580
00:41:11,580 --> 00:41:12,960
- Huh?
- Hurry!

581
00:41:13,980 --> 00:41:15,180
Yes!

582
00:41:18,143 --> 00:41:19,343
Take over!

583
00:41:20,349 --> 00:41:21,549
Yes!

584
00:41:22,842 --> 00:41:24,475
- Put on gloves!
- Okay!

585
00:41:28,820 --> 00:41:30,053
I'll take over!

586
00:41:43,523 --> 00:41:44,723
Insulin?!

587
00:41:44,850 --> 00:41:46,936
She's diabetic?!

588
00:41:47,070 --> 00:41:48,850
Without insulin injections,

589
00:41:49,023 --> 00:41:52,016
ketoacidosis led to hyperkalemia,
resulting in cardiac arrest.

590
00:42:00,493 --> 00:42:01,693
It's broken!

591
00:42:01,993 --> 00:42:03,213
What?!

592
00:42:06,320 --> 00:42:07,523
No way.

593
00:42:08,946 --> 00:42:10,320
What do we do?

594
00:42:19,696 --> 00:42:21,256
Doctor!

595
00:42:25,349 --> 00:42:26,995
Found her! Over here!

596
00:42:40,236 --> 00:42:42,970
Use this! It's from the kid's mom!

597
00:43:01,260 --> 00:43:03,003
- I'll take over!
- Okay!

598
00:44:18,753 --> 00:44:20,026
Heartbeat restored!

599
00:44:23,113 --> 00:44:24,773
- Let's go!
- Yes!

600
00:44:27,999 --> 00:44:29,986
- Almost there!
- Hurry.

601
00:44:31,060 --> 00:44:32,260
Hurry!

602
00:44:32,300 --> 00:44:33,560
Hurry!

603
00:44:33,600 --> 00:44:34,726
Get movin'!

604
00:44:34,766 --> 00:44:36,300
Hurry! Hurry! Hurry!

605
00:44:56,612 --> 00:44:58,506
We barely made it!

606
00:44:58,546 --> 00:45:00,286
Just in the nick of time.

607
00:45:08,985 --> 00:45:11,460
She needs emergency surgery.
Get her to our hospital.

608
00:45:11,500 --> 00:45:12,520
I'll contact them.

609
00:45:12,560 --> 00:45:13,793
Understood!

610
00:45:19,590 --> 00:45:20,790
Doctor...

611
00:45:21,265 --> 00:45:25,830
How did you know Hina had ketoacidosis?

612
00:45:26,150 --> 00:45:27,356
The smell.

613
00:45:27,770 --> 00:45:30,130
When her breathing briefly resumed,

614
00:45:30,283 --> 00:45:31,803
I caught the ketone smell.

615
00:45:32,070 --> 00:45:35,156
Noticing a smell in that chaos...

616
00:45:36,730 --> 00:45:37,930
Oh, but...

617
00:45:38,350 --> 00:45:41,350
Why did you two bring insulin?

618
00:45:41,530 --> 00:45:43,150
We went to visit the boss,

619
00:45:43,470 --> 00:45:45,230
and the kid's mom asked us.

620
00:45:45,510 --> 00:45:47,230
Granny called her and said,

621
00:45:47,543 --> 00:45:50,069
"Send one, just in case."

622
00:45:50,463 --> 00:45:51,723
I see.

623
00:45:52,430 --> 00:45:53,656
Hey, Doc.

624
00:45:54,890 --> 00:45:56,749
We've repaid the boss's debt now.

625
00:45:57,317 --> 00:45:58,543
We're even.

626
00:46:01,369 --> 00:46:02,582
Thanks.

627
00:46:19,009 --> 00:46:20,303
Surgery in progress

628
00:46:23,080 --> 00:46:25,540
Doctor, how's Hina?

629
00:46:25,680 --> 00:46:27,780
The surgery was a success.

630
00:46:28,253 --> 00:46:30,999
Thank goodness.

631
00:46:31,080 --> 00:46:32,620
It's all thanks to you, Doctor.

632
00:46:32,920 --> 00:46:34,230
Thank you so much.

633
00:46:34,270 --> 00:46:36,245
I only did what any doctor would.

634
00:46:36,285 --> 00:46:39,499
Thank you. Thank you so much.

635
00:46:39,780 --> 00:46:41,300
Thank you.

636
00:46:41,340 --> 00:46:42,940
Aren't you going over there?

637
00:46:44,137 --> 00:46:45,373
Why?

638
00:46:46,000 --> 00:46:47,246
Well...

639
00:46:47,920 --> 00:46:50,900
You're the one
who really saved Hina, Dr. Anno.

640
00:46:51,593 --> 00:46:52,886
And yet...

641
00:46:53,230 --> 00:46:55,280
I didn't save her for the thanks.

642
00:46:57,856 --> 00:46:59,069
But still...

643
00:47:00,380 --> 00:47:01,980
You fought so hard...

644
00:47:02,480 --> 00:47:04,900
You nearly died trying to save that girl.

645
00:47:08,820 --> 00:47:11,250
Don't you deserve a little recognition?

646
00:47:13,180 --> 00:47:14,990
That child's life was saved.

647
00:47:18,299 --> 00:47:19,699
What else would I need?

648
00:47:38,030 --> 00:47:41,150
Dr. Yakushiji, do you have a moment?

649
00:47:48,899 --> 00:47:50,146
Huh?

650
00:47:51,273 --> 00:47:53,773
What's she doing here at such a late hour?

651
00:47:54,700 --> 00:47:58,720
Ms. Ogura says she really needs
to talk to you.

652
00:47:59,862 --> 00:48:01,073
What?

653
00:48:04,190 --> 00:48:09,190
I heard from the paramedics
who brought my daughter in.

654
00:48:09,942 --> 00:48:14,075
They told me everything.

655
00:48:16,350 --> 00:48:23,350
They said you saved my daughter's life.

656
00:48:29,680 --> 00:48:30,980
No, that's not right.

657
00:48:31,870 --> 00:48:33,089
What?

658
00:48:35,177 --> 00:48:37,197
I couldn't do anything.

659
00:48:39,523 --> 00:48:41,303
The one who saved Hina was...

660
00:48:43,290 --> 00:48:44,556
Dr. Anno.

661
00:48:46,390 --> 00:48:48,230
I was just standing there,

662
00:48:49,530 --> 00:48:51,783
not even knowing what to do.

663
00:48:53,596 --> 00:48:56,468
I only got in Dr. Anno's way...

664
00:48:56,508 --> 00:48:58,530
It's thanks to you, Doctor.

665
00:49:02,470 --> 00:49:09,309
Because you were brave enough
to go into that dangerous tunnel.

666
00:49:11,295 --> 00:49:15,110
That's why my daughter is alive now.

667
00:49:18,110 --> 00:49:22,023
You saved my daughter.

668
00:49:28,629 --> 00:49:34,429
Both my life and my daughter's life...

669
00:49:36,262 --> 00:49:37,908
Doctor...

670
00:49:40,342 --> 00:49:42,616
You saved us.

671
00:49:53,686 --> 00:49:56,276
Thank you so much.

672
00:50:07,096 --> 00:50:09,909
Shall we head back to your room?

673
00:50:12,403 --> 00:50:13,603
Yes.

674
00:51:18,182 --> 00:51:19,729
How's life here?

675
00:51:20,548 --> 00:51:22,123
Don't you miss America?

676
00:51:23,348 --> 00:51:25,545
Japan's not bad at all.

677
00:51:25,963 --> 00:51:27,456
I'm enjoying it.

678
00:51:28,256 --> 00:51:32,616
Lucky you. I can't say the same on my end.

679
00:51:33,990 --> 00:51:36,663
Sounds like things aren't so easy.

680
00:51:36,923 --> 00:51:38,156
Yeah.

681
00:51:38,482 --> 00:51:43,276
But I need to settle things
as soon as possible.

682
00:51:46,226 --> 00:51:47,452
The ER situation?

683
00:51:53,200 --> 00:51:57,436
By the way, you haven't decided
on your next hospital yet, right?

684
00:51:57,980 --> 00:51:59,240
No, I haven't.

685
00:52:03,113 --> 00:52:04,510
Looks like he's here.

686
00:52:19,680 --> 00:52:23,840
Thank you for going to the scene
to treat patients personally.

687
00:52:25,580 --> 00:52:30,256
However, Dr. Anno, you ignored my warning.

688
00:52:31,369 --> 00:52:35,903
As promised, you're fired.
Leave this hospital immediately.

689
00:52:56,110 --> 00:52:57,336
Dr. Tamon.

690
00:53:00,710 --> 00:53:02,583
Anno. It's been a while.

691
00:53:04,536 --> 00:53:06,630
Vice Director Tamon, what brings you here?

692
00:53:07,803 --> 00:53:11,090
I'd like you to reconsider firing Anno.

693
00:53:12,030 --> 00:53:15,135
Reconsider? You show up out
of the blue and say that?

694
00:53:15,175 --> 00:53:19,255
Anno, from now on,
you'll be assigned to Surgery.

695
00:53:21,250 --> 00:53:23,630
Surgery? What do you mean?

696
00:53:25,690 --> 00:53:28,590
Doctor, we've been expecting you.

697
00:53:34,303 --> 00:53:38,283
Thank you for the invitation.

698
00:53:39,643 --> 00:53:41,703
This is Dr. Bonten.

699
00:53:42,849 --> 00:53:46,830
Japan's top cardiac surgeon has agreed
to join us.

700
00:53:47,290 --> 00:53:48,496
At Taishaku?

701
00:53:48,542 --> 00:53:52,870
Having you here is truly reassuring, Doctor.

702
00:53:53,630 --> 00:53:56,683
Leave everything to me.

703
00:53:59,369 --> 00:54:02,796
Naomi, you should come to Taishaku, too.

704
00:54:04,296 --> 00:54:07,883
Join the surgery department with Dr. Bonten.

705
00:54:10,070 --> 00:54:12,416
What exactly are you planning?

706
00:54:14,036 --> 00:54:20,590
Oh, what do you mean? I simply want to save
as many patients as possible.

707
00:54:25,430 --> 00:54:29,136
A surgeon of your caliber is wasted
in the emergency department.

708
00:54:30,283 --> 00:54:32,623
Save patients as a surgeon.

709
00:54:32,723 --> 00:54:35,142
I'm not interested.
I belong in emergency medicine.

710
00:54:35,182 --> 00:54:38,550
I came back
to make the new hospital a reality.

711
00:54:39,090 --> 00:54:43,290
To that end,
the unprofitable ER will be shut down soon.

712
00:54:50,836 --> 00:54:54,869
I intend to close the Emergency Department.

713
00:55:24,903 --> 00:55:25,903
Next Episode Preview

714
00:55:25,929 --> 00:55:28,020
Our policy is to refuse critical patients!

715
00:55:28,060 --> 00:55:29,880
We can force him out.

716
00:55:29,936 --> 00:55:31,740
Hesitation on the battlefield is fatal.

717
00:55:31,780 --> 00:55:33,485
You're the only one here, Tamotsu!

718
00:55:33,525 --> 00:55:35,260
But I can't do it!

719
00:55:35,260 --> 00:55:37,226
You need to keep living. Hang in there.

720
00:55:37,266 --> 00:55:39,780
I will save you
from this battlefield. I promise.
